{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1e113e35-e621-466c-b79c-3528b378dc50","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Update package references** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n```\n\n**2. Enable the test platform** by adding this property:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Run tests** with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\nOr run the test project directly as an executable (Microsoft.Testing.Platform makes your test project a standalone app):\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project YourTests.csproj -- --help\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- Keep `xunit` (2.9.3) — only the *runner* changes.\n- The `xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform` package replaces `xunit.runner.visualstudio`.\n- No code changes needed in your tests themselves.\n- You gain direct-execution support, better parallel orchestration, and the new `--` CLI options.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"201cfe6a-d711-4196-840a-45a6782780d8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":367,"requestId":"BC2F:214B1C:1B1A7D6:1E24F91:69FA8F75"},"id":"31c58e39-b362-4a50-b16f-4c97b3b8ffc3","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:46:54.602Z","parentId":"28226d6e-6400-4b36-843f-555054a9dacb"}
